{"title":"Reality Demands","author":{"name":"Wisława Szymborska Translated by Stanislaw Baranczak and Clare Cavanagh"},"publishDate":"2013-04-20","lines":[{"line":"Reality demands","stanza":1,"number":1},{"line":"that we also mention this:","stanza":1,"number":2},{"line":"Life goes on.","stanza":1,"number":3},{"line":"It continues at Cannae and Borodino,","stanza":1,"number":4},{"line":"at Kosovo Polje and Guernica.","stanza":1,"number":5},{"line":"There’s a gas station","stanza":2,"number":6},{"line":"on a little square in Jericho,","stanza":2,"number":7},{"line":"and wet paint","stanza":2,"number":8},{"line":"on park benches in Bila Hora.","stanza":2,"number":9},{"line":"Letters fly back and forth","stanza":2,"number":10},{"line":"between Pearl Harbor and Hastings,","stanza":2,"number":11},{"line":"a moving van passes","stanza":2,"number":12},{"line":"beneath the eye of the lion at Chaeronea,","stanza":2,"number":13},{"line":"and the blooming orchards near Verdun","stanza":2,"number":14},{"line":"cannot escape","stanza":2,"number":15},{"line":"the approaching atmospheric front.","stanza":2,"number":16},{"line":"There is so much Everything","stanza":3,"number":17},{"line":"that Nothing is hidden quite nicely.","stanza":3,"number":18},{"line":"Music pours","stanza":3,"number":19},{"line":"from the yachts moored at Actium","stanza":3,"number":20},{"line":"and couples dance on the sunlit decks.","stanza":3,"number":21},{"line":"So much is always going on,","stanza":4,"number":22},{"line":"that it must be going on all over.","stanza":4,"number":23},{"line":"Where not a stone still stands,","stanza":4,"number":24},{"line":"you see the Ice Cream Man","stanza":4,"number":25},{"line":"besieged by children.","stanza":4,"number":26},{"line":"Where Hiroshima had been","stanza":4,"number":27},{"line":"Hiroshima is again,","stanza":4,"number":28},{"line":"producing many products","stanza":4,"number":29},{"line":"for everyday use.","stanza":4,"number":30},{"line":"This terrifying world is not devoid of charms,","stanza":4,"number":31},{"line":"of the mornings","stanza":4,"number":32},{"line":"that make waking up worthwhile.","stanza":4,"number":33},{"line":"The grass is green","stanza":5,"number":34},{"line":"on Maciejowice’s fields,","stanza":5,"number":35},{"line":"and it is studded with dew,","stanza":5,"number":36},{"line":"as is normal grass.","stanza":5,"number":37},{"line":"Perhaps all fields are battlefields,","stanza":6,"number":38},{"line":"those we remember","stanza":6,"number":39},{"line":"and those that are forgotten:","stanza":6,"number":40},{"line":"the birch forests and the cedar forests,","stanza":6,"number":41},{"line":"the snow and the sand, the iridescent swamps","stanza":6,"number":42},{"line":"and the canyons of black defeat,","stanza":6,"number":43},{"line":"where now, when the need strikes, you don’t cower","stanza":6,"number":44},{"line":"under a bush but squat behind it.","stanza":6,"number":45},{"line":"What moral flows from this? Probably none.","stanza":7,"number":46},{"line":"Only that blood flows, drying quickly,","stanza":7,"number":47},{"line":"and, as always, a few rivers, a few clouds.","stanza":7,"number":48},{"line":"On tragic mountain passes","stanza":8,"number":49},{"line":"the wind rips hats from unwitting heads","stanza":8,"number":50},{"line":"and we can’t help","stanza":8,"number":51},{"line":"laughing at that.","stanza":8,"number":52}]}